
[1]unbelief

   UNBELIE'F, n.

   1. Incredulity; the withholding of belief; as, unbelief is blind.

   2. Infidelity; disbelief of divine revelation.

   3. In the New Testament, disbelief of the truth of the gospel,
   rejection of Christ as the Savior of men, and of the doctrines he
   taught; distrust of God's promises and faithfulness, &c. Matt. 13. Mark
   16. Heb. 3. Rom. 4.

   4. Weak faith. Mark 9.
